## Confusion Matrix Explanation
[[82 17]
 [21 34]]

82 (True Negatives) : Correctly predicted non-diabetic patients
34 (True Positives) : Correctly predicted diabetic patients
17 (False Positives) : Predicted diabetic, but actually not diabetic
21 (False Negatives) : Predicted non-diabetic, but actually diabetic

##Accuracy
The model achieved an accuracy of 75.32%
This means the model correctly predicted diabetes outcome for about 75 out of 100 patients

